            "title": "General Motors raises dividend by 20% to $0.18, announces $6B buyback",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>General Motors (GM) declares <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20376776-gm-releases-2025-financial-results-and-2026-guidance-board-declares-dividend-at-20-percent\">$0.18/share quarterly dividend</a>, <font color=\"green\">20% increase</font> from prior dividend of $0.15.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GM/dividends/yield?source=news_bullet\">Forward yield</a> 0.91%</li>\n<li>Payable March 19; for shareholders of record March 6; ex-div March 6.</li>\n<li>The company also announced that its Board has approved a new $6.0 billion share repurchase authorization.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GM/dividends?source=news_bullet\">See GM Dividend Scorecard, Yield Chart, &amp; Dividend Growth.</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
