            "id": "4542778",
            "title": "UnitedHealth tumbles as Q4 results add to managed care misery",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">UnitedHealth Group (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UNH\" title=\"UnitedHealth Group Incorporated\">UNH</a></span>) fell sharply alongside its managed care peers in the premarket on Tuesday after the healthcare giant’s Q4 revenue and full-year revenue outlook fell short of Street forecasts, pressuring an industry reeling from an unfavorable Medicare rate decision.</p>\n<p>The Eden Prairie, Minnesota-based health insurer, the number one player in the Medicare Advantage market, lost ~12%, while Humana (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HUM\" title=\"Humana Inc.\">HUM</a>), the second-largest, declined by ~14%. Other notable decliners included CVS Health (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CVS\" title=\"CVS Health Corporation\">CVS</a>), Cigna (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CI\" title=\"The Cigna Group\">CI</a>), Clover Health (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CLOV\" title=\"Clover Health Investments, Corp.\">CLOV</a>), and Alignment Healthcare (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ALHC\" title=\"Alignment Healthcare, Inc.\">ALHC</a>).</p>\n<p>UnitedHealth (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UNH\" title=\"UnitedHealth Group Incorporated\">UNH</a>) reported $2.11 of adjusted earnings per share for the quarter, in line with the consensus, while its Q4 revenue stood at $113.2B, falling short of Street forecasts by $520M despite <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4542767-unitedhealth-non-gaap-eps-of-2_11-in-line-revenue-of-113_21b-misses-by-520m\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">~12% YoY growth.</a></p>\n<p>As for the 2026 outlook, the company projects adjusted earnings per share of over $17.75, roughly in line with the $17.76 projected by analysts, on more than $439B in revenue, which fell short of the <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20376719-unitedhealth-group-reports-2025-results-and-issues-2026-outlook\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">consensus of about $456.0B.</a></p>\n<p>Late on Monday, the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services ((CMS)) proposed roughly flat reimbursement rates for Medicare Advantage insurers in 2027, pressuring managed care stocks<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4542683-humana-other-insurers-fall-on-flat-rates-for-medicaid-advantage-payments-in-2027\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"> in the post-market.</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/author/edmund-ingham\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Edmund Ingham</a>, Seeking Alpha’s Investing Group Leader for Haggerston BioHealth, argued that UNH’s earnings marked “a somewhat disastrous start to the new year for America's largest health insurer.”</p>\n<p>\"It looks as though UnitedHealth shareholders are in for more pain after a tough 2025, which saw shares decline in value by ~30%,\" Ingham added.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4542778-unitedhealth-stock-tumbles-q4-results",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-27 19:52:54",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
